  "_about": "Nine Steps for the discover-project Workflow per TDD §Canonical Identifiers — Step ULIDs and §Form (5-phase decomposition). Each Step declares the IDEF0 contract (input_artifacts + output_artifacts + mechanism) plus the Tool it invokes (tool_ref) and the FailureModes it handles (handles_failures). Phase grouping is encoded in mechanism_detail (Detect/Infer/Ask/Mint/Verify) because the brain Step schema sets unevaluatedProperties:false and the foundation Step schema does not carry a per-Step phase field — extending the foundation schema is a cross-repo concern out of scope here, same pattern as release-train steps.jsonld. for_workflow lives at the envelope (not per-Step) for the same schema-constraint reason. Steps 1-4 are the Detect phase. Step 5 is the only probabilistic Step (mechanism=probabilistic, MUC-008 token-budget guard at 10k per NFR-002 + ADR-006). Steps 6-7 are the Ask phase (mechanism=human). Step 8 is the Mint phase atomic write (MUC-002 cancellation safety, MUC-003 existence check, MUC-007 monorepo collision check). Step 9 is the Verify phase scoped drift invocation (MUC-005 roll-back on failure). Tenant + workflow ULIDs are byte-identical to TDD §Canonical Identifiers and shared across every discover-project canonical instance.",
  "captured_on": "2026-06-01",

